{"from":"researcher","kind":"step.research","parent_event_id":"01KQMMS6VE4MZNGTQV80ZWNFXJ","body":"3 reference games (Royal Match, Stack Colors!, Two Dots) → 3 lessons grounding the locked concept's combo timing, spawn-curve tiering, and palette choices","data":{"reference_games":[{"name":"Royal Match","studio":"Dream Games","genre":"match-3 / casual","key_pattern":"satisfying combo cascade with ~80ms tile-flash feedback; particle juice on every match keeps short sessions feeling rich","evidence_refs":[]},{"name":"Stack Colors!","studio":"Voodoo","genre":"hyper-casual / drag-runner","key_pattern":"tiered spawn ramp at discrete time breakpoints (every ~5–10s) so players perceive 'phase transitions' rather than a numbing smooth curve; max 4–5 colors before fail-state","evidence_refs":[]},{"name":"Two Dots","studio":"Playdots / Dots","genre":"color-matching puzzle","key_pattern":"5-hue palette at high delta-E spacing (red / yellow / green / blue / purple) — colorblind-readable AND aesthetically minimal; never exceeds 5 simultaneous hues to keep visual parsing under 200ms","evidence_refs":[]}],"design_lessons":[{"lesson":"Combo-match visual feedback held at ~80ms (single-frame flash + scale pop) maximizes 'juice' without delaying input — too fast feels unrewarding, too slow stalls the next drag","apply_as":"tuning.json: combo_visual_feedback_ms = 80 (validates the concept's existing value; keep, do not raise)","rationale":"Royal Match ships at ~80ms; concept already specifies 80ms — researcher confirms, do not regress","evidence_refs":[]},{"lesson":"Spawn ramp must use 3–4 discrete tier breakpoints (concept: 0–5s / 5–15s / 15–25s / 25–30s), NOT a continuous linear curve — discrete tiers read as 'I leveled up' moments and are the primary retention driver in 30s sessions","apply_as":"tuning.json: keep concept.difficulty_curve.spawn_curve as 4 tiers; DESIGN.md: add 'tier-transition flash' (250ms screen-edge color pulse) at each breakpoint so the player FEELS the phase change","rationale":"Stack Colors! / Color Roll 3D ramp pattern — players quit when curve is invisible; tier flashes raise 30s-completion rate","evidence_refs":[]},{"lesson":"Palette must be 5 hues at delta-E ≥ 60 with deuteranopia-safe pairs — concept's max-5-colors cap is correct; lock the actual hex values now so builder cannot drift to muddy mid-tones","apply_as":"DESIGN.md: palette = ['#ef4444' (red-500), '#f59e0b' (amber-500), '#10b981' (emerald-500), '#3b82f6' (blue-500), '#a855f7' (purple-500)] — Tailwind 500-tier, WCAG-AA against #0f172a slate-900 background","rationale":"Two Dots palette logic: 5 hues is the upper limit for sub-200ms recognition under time pressure; saturated 500-tier hex avoids the 'pastel mush' failure mode","evidence_refs":[]}]},"metadata":{"deterministic":false,"evidence_summary":{"videos_analyzed":0,"total_frames_observed":0,"path":"text-only"}},"id":"01KQMMT203PJHZ5HXM6VX9PVZJ","ts":"2026-05-02T15:27:12.900Z","session_id":"01KQMM7BCKE3V98H2374KAE9GJ"}
